[src:kubernetes-security-hardening/microservices] With microservices, only the microservice supporting the function with resource constraints needs to be scaled out, thus providing resource and cost optimization benefits.
[src:kubernetes-security-hardening/microservices] Despite its benefits, microservices architecture introduces challenges such as increased operational complexity, network latency, and the need for robust monitoring and fault tolerance mechanisms.
[src:kubernetes-security-hardening/microservices] Cell-based architecture is a distributed computing design in which computational resources are organized into self-contained units called cells.
